# Applications — document sync

Final deliverables live only in each project's `documents/` folder and stay fully in sync. Layout: `.cursor/rules/folder_structure.mdc`.

## Sync set (per project)

| Format | Filename pattern |
|---|---|
| PDF | `{project}_pdf.pdf` |
| PowerPoint | `{project}_ppt.pptx` |
| Word | `{project}_word.docx` |

Examples: `awief_pdf.pdf`, `fid_ppt.pptx`, `awief_word.docx`.

## Sync rules

1. Edit one format → update the other two in the same session (story, data, branding, compliance).
2. Regenerate only with **that project's** build script(s). Never stamp many projects from a shared factory.
3. Prefer the most recently edited format; if unclear, follow the project SoT (e.g. AWIEF → `refined_project_idea.md`).
4. Keep only the three official files in `documents/` — no drafts or renamed copies.
5. Use images from `assets/` (or a project `assets/` folder). Keep brand look consistent across formats.
6. Before an external submission, meet all eligibility, theme, format, and deadline rules.
7. Keep line spacing clear in Word, PPT, and PDF — no overlapping text.
8. **Cover / first page:** Programme or document title, FairBanks/FCHIP framing, slogan (**Your health, our mission.**), and visuals as needed. Add an application-details table on the cover only if the call requires it.

## PowerPoint — `{project}_ppt.pptx` (elegant by default)

Treat every deck as a polished visual product, not a text dump. Slides should look intentional, attractive, and easy to follow live.

1. **Balance & type:** Size text for the space. On photo+text slides, grow and centre body text so it matches the photo’s weight. No tiny type in empty space; no crowding or overlap.
2. **Pictures first:** Prefer real photos, diagrams, maps, and dashboards from `assets/` over long paragraphs. One clear image idea per slide.
3. **Visual design:** Brand colours, clean margins, consistent headers/footers, calm contrast. Vary layouts (full-bleed cover, split photo/text, cards, process flows) so the deck feels designed.
4. **Motion with purpose:** Light, tasteful animations (fade, wipe, appear) on titles, key bullets, and photo entrances where they help. Subtle and consistent — never noisy.
5. **Readability check:** Before finishing, scan every slide: clear hierarchy, even spacing, sharp images, readable at distance, elegant and on-brand.

## Sources of truth

- Call rules: `applications/{project}/rules/source_of_truth.mdc`
- Opportunities: `opportunities/rules/source_of_truth.mdc`

Follow the official call when unsure. One rules tree per project (globs, not always-on).
